JavaScript Program to Count Vowels in a String
HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<script>
function countVowels(str) {
    let count = 0;

    for(let i = 0; i < str.length; i++) {
        if("aeiouAEIOU".includes(str[i])) {
            count++;
        }
    }

    return count;
}

let result = countVowels("Payal");
document.write("Number of vowels = " + result);
</script>

</body>
</html>
Output
Number of vowels = 2

Explanation:

countVowels() accepts a string as an argument.

It checks each character.

If the character is a vowel (a, e, i, o, u), the count increases.

Finally, it returns the total number of vowels. ✅

