Explain Web Server Creation in Node.js

A web server is used to handle client requests and send responses through a web browser. In Node.js, a web server is created using the built-in http module.

Steps to Create a Web Server

Import the http module.

Create a server using createServer().

Write a response using res.write().

End the response using res.end().

Start the server using listen().

Program
JavaScript
const http = require('http');

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
    res.write("Hello World");
    res.end();
});

server.listen(3000, () => {
    console.log("Server Running on Port 3000");
});
Output

Browser:

Hello World

Console:

Server Running on Port 3000
Conclusion

Node.js creates web servers using the http module. The server listens for requests and sends responses to the client.

